  "text": "Group 1 comprised a group of 19 dogs diagnosed with idiopathic IBD according to previously published criteria [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The enrollment criteria included persistent (> 3 weeks duration) GI signs, failure to respond to appropriate dietary (elimination diet fed exclusively for at least 3 weeks) and antibiotic (metronidazole or tylosin administered exclusively for 14 days or more) trials, failure to document other causes for gastroenteritis by thorough diagnostic testing, and histopathologic evidence of mucosal inflammation observed in endoscopic biopsies.",
